"milestone": null, "comments": 6, "created_at": "2017-12-12T11:33:48Z", "updated_at": "2018-01-24T19:24:02Z", "closed_at": "2018-01-24T19:24:01Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/pulls/15307", "html_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/15307", "diff_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/15307.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/15307.patch"}, "body_html": "<p>Setting proper soname prevents from linking with absolute path when using <code>cmake</code>.</p>\n<p>The reference below contains long conversation about the issue with linking, but the general idea is when a library has no <code>DT_SONAME</code> field, executable is linked with absolute path and can't be used in a different environment, setting <code>LD_LIBRARY_PATH</code> doesn't help.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://cmake.3232098.n2.nabble.com/How-to-avoid-the-explicit-library-location-when-linking-with-imported-library-targets-td5542269.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://cmake.3232098.n2.nabble.com/How-to-avoid-the-explicit-library-location-when-linking-with-imported-library-targets-td5542269.html</a></p>", "body_text": "Setting proper soname prevents from linking with absolute path when using cmake.\nThe reference below contains long conversation about the issue with linking, but the general idea is when a library has no DT_SONAME field, executable is linked with absolute path and can't be used in a different environment, setting LD_LIBRARY_PATH doesn't help.\nhttp://cmake.3232098.n2.nabble.com/How-to-avoid-the-explicit-library-location-when-linking-with-imported-library-targets-td5542269.html", "body": "Setting proper soname prevents from linking with absolute path when using `cmake`.\r\n\r\nThe reference below contains long conversation about the issue with linking, but the general idea is when a library has no `DT_SONAME` field, executable is linked with absolute path and can't be used in a different environment, setting `LD_LIBRARY_PATH` doesn't help.\r\n\r\nhttp://cmake.3232098.n2.nabble.com/How-to-avoid-the-explicit-library-location-when-linking-with-imported-library-targets-td5542269.html"}